JNC 15/May/25
Added option to copy all of the data, regardless of where the burst signal is, flipped the sign of the visibilities to match test observations of offset sources, minor changes in parsing of svfits_par.txt file, some plotting programs. Added some documentation in the SVFITS.md markdown file.


Some details on the files in this commit are given below.

antsamp.hdr - No change

fitsio.h  No change

longnam.h No Change

makefile No change

newcorr.h No change

plot_flagged.py  No change

plot_postcorr.py added making a plot of the de-dispersed time series and showing the burse-time given by the trigger software, and other minor changes.

Readme -- this file.

read_rawvis.py minor changes to the way the plots are titled.

stats.c -- No change

SVFITS.md  markdown file with some user docummentation

svfits.c -- added a mode where all of the input data is converted to UVFITS regardless of where the burst signal lies. 

svfits_par.txt -- updated to include the parameters to allow for all of the data to be converted to fits (ALL_DATA,NCHAV)

svio.h -- small changes corresponding to the new options in svfits.

svsubs.c -- increased the maximum size of the command line option parameters, and also flipped the visibility sign to match the observed position of the offset source in test observations.

utils.c -- No change
